凭什么知道我的健康状况呢?
know about my health?

9
00:02:29,646 --> 00:02:30,667
福尔摩斯 听着
Listen, Holmes,

10
00:02:30,704 --> 00:02:33,621
Moor Agar医生坚持要你彻底休息一下
Doctor Moor Agar insists you have a complete rests

11
00:02:33,658 --> 00:02:36,918
否则你的身体就要完全垮掉了
if you wish to avoid an absolute breakdown.

12
00:02:37,727 --> 00:02:40,272
海边的空气对你的健康有利
The sea air will do you the world of good.

13
00:02:42,552 --> 00:02:45,076
你该独自旅行的 华生
You should have traveled alone, Watson.

14
00:02:45,155 --> 00:02:46,644
胡说
Nonsense.

15
00:02:46,723 --> 00:02:48,691
你在休假中
You're on holiday.

16
00:03:16,617 --> 00:03:19,449
太美妙了 福尔摩斯 简直太美妙了
Why it's wonderful, Holmes, wonderful!

17
00:03:19,519 --> 00:03:21,578
这里的景色真是壮观
The views are spectacular.

18
00:03:21,655 --> 00:03:23,679
我们正处在
Well we're looking at the most dangerous piece

19
00:03:23,757 --> 00:03:25,987
我国最险峻的一处海岸线
of coastline in the country.

20
00:03:26,059 --> 00:03:28,822
你的朋友是位自然历史学家?
Your friend is a natural historian I presume?

21
00:03:28,895 --> 00:03:31,420
大学时代的老相识
An old acquaintance from my college days.

22
00:03:42,274 --> 00:03:44,104
我去看下行李
I'll see to the luggage.

23
00:03:44,175 --> 00:03:45,938
谢谢
Thank you.

24
00:03:50,115 --> 00:03:52,236
你好 先生
Good day to you, sir.

25
00:03:53,918 --> 00:03:56,818
我想之后几周
I thought as we were going to be neighbors

26
00:03:56,888 --> 00:03:58,252
我们会成为邻居
for the next few weeks

27
00:03:58,323 --> 00:04:00,086
我应当来欢迎一下
I ought to say a few words of welcome.

28
00:04:00,158 --> 00:04:01,488
真是客气
How very kind.

29
00:04:01,558 --> 00:04:03,651
而且我当然渴望见到
And of course I've long wanted to meet

30
00:04:03,728 --> 00:04:05,388
夏洛克 福尔摩斯先生
Mr. Sherlock Holmes.

31
00:04:05,462 --> 00:04:07,191
先生 我真的很荣幸
It is indeed a pleasure, sir.

32
00:04:07,264 --> 00:04:10,596
谢谢 但我是约翰 华生医生
Thank you but I'm Doctor John Watson.

33
00:04:10,666 --> 00:04:11,928
哦
Oh.

34
00:04:15,343 --> 00:04:16,664
请进
Come in.

35
00:04:18,875 --> 00:04:21,400
这是我的好朋友 夏洛克 福尔摩斯
This is my good friend Sherlock Holmes.

36
00:04:21,476 --> 00:04:23,602
非常抱歉我本该意识到
A thousand apologies, I should have realized.

37
00:04:23,678 --> 00:04:25,338
请进吧 Roundhay先生
Do come in Mr. Roundhay.

38
00:04:25,413 --> 00:04:28,109
我真是太蠢了
Very stupid of me.

39
00:04:28,183 --> 00:04:30,650
您怎么知道我的名字的?
How did you know my name?

40
00:04:30,719 --> 00:04:33,551
你对考古很感兴趣是吗?
You have an interest in archeology do you not?

41
00:04:33,622 --> 00:04:34,953
你怎么知道的?
Why yes.

42
00:04:35,023 --> 00:04:37,217
华生 你来继续...
Deduce, Watson, go on.

43
00:04:37,292 --> 00:04:39,692
推理
Deduce.

44
00:04:39,761 --> 00:04:41,991
你鞋尖上 膝盖下面
You've got mud on the points of your shoes

45
00:04:42,063 --> 00:04:44,553
和右手上
and beneath your knees

46
00:04:44,632 --> 00:04:46,964
都沾有泥土
and on the fingers of your right hand...

47
00:04:47,034 --> 00:04:48,436
太精彩了
Splendid, splendid.

48
00:04:48,473 --> 00:04:50,666
这说明你之前跪了一段时间在地上
Which indicates that you've knelt on the ground for a length of time.

49
00:04:50,703 --> 00:04:52,155
华生 你越来越不可思议了
Oh Watson, you're coming along marvelously.

50
00:04:52,192 --> 00:04:53,359
你是个左撇子园丁
You're a left-handed gardener.

51
00:04:53,396 --> 00:04:55,126
还是考古专业的学生
You're a student of archeology.

52
00:04:55,473 --> 00:04:57,866
你发表了一篇关于新石器时代
You've published a paper over theories

53
00:04:57,944 --> 00:04:59,275
埋葬风俗的文章
surrounding the neolithic burial rites.

54
00:04:59,345 --> 00:05:03,769
您 尊敬的Francis Roundhay 还是当地教区的牧师
You are the Reverend Francis Roundhay, vicar of the parish.

55
00:05:05,451 --> 00:05:08,385
太惊人了 先生
Astonishing, sir.

56
00:05:08,454 --> 00:05:10,455
-请坐 -谢谢
-Please sit down. -Thank you.

57
00:05:11,973 --> 00:05:14,482
但左撇子...
But left-handed?

58
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:18,655
你拿钓绳的那只手
The hand with which you hold the troll.

59
00:05:18,730 --> 00:05:20,196
完全正确
Exactly right.

60
00:05:20,265 --> 00:05:22,459
每个细节都准确无误 但是你是怎么
Precise in every detail but how sir?

61
00:05:22,533 --> 00:05:23,897
怎么知道
How?

62
00:05:23,969 --> 00:05:25,457
教区牧师...
Vicar, vicar vic...

63
00:05:25,536 --> 00:05:26,468
这本教区的杂志...
the parish magazine has...

64
00:05:36,347 --> 00:05:37,779
村子就在这附近吗?
The village is nearby?

65
00:05:37,848 --> 00:05:40,111
是的 沿着滨海小道就能走到
Oh yes just along the coastal path.

66
00:05:40,183 --> 00:05:42,844
村子很偏僻 但能满足我们全部所需
It's secluded but it caters for all our needs.

67
00:05:42,919 --> 00:05:44,564
那是最近的居所吗?
I suppose is that the nearest habitation?

68
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:46,910
不 不 还有Tregennis家的房子
No, no, the Tregennis Estate

69
00:05:46,990 --> 00:05:48,456
就在内陆一英里处
is about a mile inland.

70
00:05:48,525 --> 00:05:49,957
非常和善的一家
Very nice people

71
00:05:50,026 --> 00:05:51,356
我相信他们会向你展示
and I'm sure they'll extend to you

72
00:05:51,427 --> 00:05:55,328
康沃尔人的热情好客
some fine Cornish hospitality.

73
00:05:55,398 --> 00:05:55,910
不过...
However,

74
00:05:55,947 --> 00:05:59,031
我已经打扰你们太久了
I've imposed enough upon you for one day.

75
00:05:59,101 --> 00:06:00,465
或许你们愿意
Perhaps you'd care to

76
00:06:00,536 --> 00:06:01,797
来我的住处
come and have dinner with me

77
00:06:01,870 --> 00:06:03,167
共进晚餐?
one evening at the vicarage.

78
00:06:03,238 --> 00:06:05,638
那我们就要打扰到你和你的家人了
Oh then we should impose upon you and your family?

79
00:06:05,707 --> 00:06:07,402
哦不会的 我是单身
Oh no alas, I have no family.

80
00:06:07,476 --> 00:06:09,306
我和Tregennis先生住在一起
I live alone except for Mr. Tregennis,

81
00:06:09,377 --> 00:06:11,173
他住其中的一间
who has a suite of rooms in the house.

82
00:06:11,246 --> 00:06:13,611
他为什么不住在自家房子里?
But does he not live on the estate?

83
00:06:13,681 --> 00:06:15,341
家庭不合
A family dispute.

84
00:06:15,416 --> 00:06:17,076
他的妹妹和两个兄弟住在那儿
His sister and two brothers live there

85
00:06:17,151 --> 00:06:19,243
但他选择搬出来
but he chooses to live apart.

86
00:06:19,320 --> 00:06:25,382
去牧师家里共进晚餐
Do you know dinner at the vicarage

87
00:06:25,459 --> 00:06:28,930
是个很好的主意
is a splendid idea.

88
00:06:29,008 --> 00:06:30,987
我们得安排一下时间
We must arrange a date.

89
00:06:35,067 --> 00:06:37,762
那是当然的 先生们
Yes, well of course gentlemen,

90
00:06:37,837 --> 00:06:39,963
祝你们过得愉快
good day to you.

91
00:07:05,629 --> 00:07:07,336
早上好
Good morning.

92
00:07:12,168 --> 00:07:16,297
康沃尔人的热情好客
Cornish hospitality.

93
00:07:16,372 --> 00:07:20,034
风化后凹凸不平的花岗岩
Weathered pitted slabs of granite.

94
00:07:20,109 --> 00:07:23,442
古时的坟墓散布在
Ancient tombs scattered throughout

95
00:07:23,513 --> 00:07:26,072
这个半岛冗长的岁月里
the lengthened breath of this peninsula.

96
00:07:26,149 --> 00:07:28,845
就像大海
Like the sea.

97
00:07:28,917 --> 00:07:32,910
我想死亡始终如影随形吧
I suppose death is always with us.

98
00:07:38,193 --> 00:07:40,023
是啊
Quite so.

99
00:07:57,444 --> 00:07:59,809
在康沃尔的这些日子里
Quite often during those days in Cornwall,

100
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:02,507
福尔摩斯常常独自出行
Holmes would stride out alone.

101
00:08:02,582 --> 00:08:05,414
此地的神秘与魅力
The mystery and glamour of the place

102
00:08:05,485 --> 00:08:08,269
以及被遗忘的民族留下的不祥之气
with its sinister atmosphere of forgotten nations

103
00:08:08,306 --> 00:08:12,285
吸引着我这位朋友的想象力
appeal to the imagination of my friend.

104
00:08:12,458 --> 00:08:15,154
他花很长时间漫步
He spent much of his time in long walks

105
00:08:15,227 --> 00:08:17,769
独自冥想
and solitary meditation.

106
00:09:01,771 --> 00:09:03,431
然而在一个早晨
One morning however,

107
00:09:03,506 --> 00:09:05,030
我朋友的恢复疗养
my friend's convalescence

108
00:09:05,107 --> 00:09:07,802
被粗暴地打断了
was violently interrupted.

109
00:09:09,210 --> 00:09:11,201
先生们 我强烈建议你们求助于警方
Gentlemen I urge you to consult the police.

110
00:09:11,279 --> 00:09:13,246
福尔摩斯是位病人
Holmes is a sick man.

111
00:09:13,314 --> 00:09:18,341
是的 但在渐渐康复中 华生
Yes but getting better all the time, Watson.

112
00:09:21,422 --> 00:09:24,823
是有紧急事件发生吧
This is a matter of some emergency.

113
00:09:24,892 --> 00:09:26,052
福尔摩斯先生
Mr. Holmes,

114
00:09:26,126 --> 00:09:27,421
福尔摩斯先生
Mr. Holmes,

115
00:09:27,494 --> 00:09:28,755
我们只能将您
we can only regard it

116
00:09:28,829 --> 00:09:30,126
恰巧出现在此时此地
as a special Providence

117
00:09:30,197 --> 00:09:32,255
看做是上天的特别眷顾
that you should chance to be here at this time,

118
00:09:32,331 --> 00:09:34,060
因为在整个英格兰
for in all England

119
00:09:34,134 --> 00:09:35,623
你是我们唯一真正需要的人
you are the one man we truly need.

120
00:09:35,701 --> 00:09:37,191
我试图跟Trengennis先生
I tried to explain to Mr. Tregennis

121
00:09:37,270 --> 00:09:38,463
和Roundhay先生解释
and Mr. Roundhay

122
00:09:38,538 --> 00:09:40,301
说你在疗养
that you're in convalescence.

123
00:09:40,373 --> 00:09:42,033
我相信他们一定赞成
Yes I'm sure they'll be very sympathetic,

124
00:09:42,108 --> 00:09:43,369
请坐
please sit down.

125
00:09:43,443 --> 00:09:45,466
谢谢
Thank you.

126
00:09:45,544 --> 00:09:46,737
事实上
The fact is,

127
00:09:46,813 --> 00:09:48,780
正如我向华生医生所解释的
as I've explained to Doctor Watson,

128
00:09:48,847 --> 00:09:51,839
一件异常骇人的悲剧
the most extraordinary and tragic affair

129
00:09:51,918 --> 00:09:53,941
昨晚发生在这里
has occurred here during the night.

130
00:09:54,019 --> 00:09:56,911
洗耳恭听
You have my full attention.

131
00:09:56,988 --> 00:09:59,547
我应该先介绍一下
Perhaps I had better say a few words first.

132
00:09:59,624 --> 00:10:01,319
这位是我曾提到的
This is Mr. Tregennis,

133
00:10:01,392 --> 00:10:03,155
Tregennis先生
of whom I spoke.

134
00:10:03,227 --> 00:10:06,821
Tregennis先生昨晚
Now Mr. Tregennis spent last night

135
00:10:06,897 --> 00:10:08,296
与他的兄弟
in the company of his brother,

136
00:10:08,365 --> 00:10:09,854
George和Owen
George and Owen,

137
00:10:09,934 --> 00:10:11,400
以及妹妹Brenda一同
and his sister Brenda,

138
00:10:11,469 --> 00:10:13,699
在Tredannick Wartha的房子里
at their house of Tredannick Wartha.

139
00:10:13,770 --> 00:10:15,362
他走的时候
He left them,

140
00:10:15,438 --> 00:10:16,735
他们围坐在餐桌前玩牌
playing cards around the dining table

141
00:10:16,806 --> 00:10:20,241
身体和精神状态都很好
in excellent health and spirits.

142
00:10:20,310 --> 00:10:22,504
但他今天早上回去的时候
But on his return this morning

143
00:10:22,579 --> 00:10:26,742
发现情形极其诡异
he discovered a truly bizarre state of affairs.

144
00:10:26,815 --> 00:10:29,147
三个人 不论生者还是死者
All three both alive and dead,

145
00:10:29,219 --> 00:10:31,084
脸上都保留着
retained upon their faces

146
00:10:31,154 --> 00:10:34,987
极度恐惧的表情
an expression of the utmost horror.

147
00:10:35,057 --> 00:10:37,024
死者呢?
Dead?

148
00:10:37,093 --> 00:10:38,865
死于惊恐
A convulsion of terror.

149
00:10:41,897 --> 00:10:46,162
惨不忍睹
It was dreadful to look upon.

150
00:10:46,234 --> 00:10:48,428
房里还有其它人吗?
Was there any sign of anyone else in the house?

151
00:10:48,503 --> 00:10:50,198
只有Porter女士
Only Mrs. Porter,

152
00:10:50,271 --> 00:10:52,431
她是厨师兼管家
cook and housekeeper.

153
00:10:52,507 --> 00:10:53,940
她昨晚睡得很沉
She had slept deeply

154
00:10:54,008 --> 00:10:56,271
没听见任何声响
and heard no sound in the night.

155
00:10:56,343 --> 00:11:00,176
有什么异常被遗漏了吗?
Is anything missing, disarranged?

156
00:11:00,247 --> 00:11:02,340
没有 福尔摩斯先生
Nothing, Mr. Holmes.

157
00:11:02,415 --> 00:11:03,608
是怎样的恐惧
What could possibly

158
00:11:03,684 --> 00:11:05,048
能够让一位青年女子死亡
frighten a young woman to death

159
00:11:05,118 --> 00:11:06,277
让两位壮汉疯掉呢?
and two strong men out of their senses?

160
00:11:06,353 --> 00:11:07,684
嗯 会是什么呢
Yes what indeed.

161
00:11:07,754 --> 00:11:10,620
福尔摩斯 我相信本地警方
Well I'm sure, Holmes, that the local police

162
00:11:10,657 --> 00:11:12,455
将会得出结论
would have reached some conclusions.

163
00:11:12,525 --> 00:11:14,254
但很可能是不正确的
However, erroneous they may be.

164
00:11:14,327 --> 00:11:16,157
福尔摩斯
Holmes.

165
00:11:16,228 --> 00:11:17,558
想一想
Think.

166
00:11:17,630 --> 00:11:21,623
告诉我昨晚的情况 Tregennis先生
Tell me about last night, Mr. Tregennis.

167
00:11:21,700 --> 00:11:23,564
好的 福尔摩斯先生
Well Mr. Holmes,

168
00:11:26,871 --> 00:11:28,428
我在那里吃过晚饭
I supped there,

169
00:11:28,506 --> 00:11:31,303
正如牧师所说
as the vicar has said,

170
00:11:31,376 --> 00:11:34,004
之后我的哥哥George
and my elder brother George

171
00:11:34,078 --> 00:11:38,013
提议玩一会儿扑克牌
proposed a game of whist afterwards.

172
00:11:38,082 --> 00:11:40,572
我走的时候是十点一刻
It was a quarter-past ten when I moved to go.

173
00:11:40,652 --> 00:11:42,585
谁送你出门?
Who let you out?

174
00:11:42,654 --> 00:11:44,211
Potter夫人已经睡了
Mrs. Potter had gone to bed

175
00:11:44,288 --> 00:11:45,845
所以我自己出了门
so I let myself out.

176
00:11:45,923 --> 00:11:49,153
他们所处房间的窗户都关着
The window of the room in which they sat was closed,

177
00:11:49,225 --> 00:11:52,456
但窗帘并没有拉上
but the blind was not drawn down.

178
00:11:52,528 --> 00:11:53,825
今天早上
There was no change

179
00:11:53,896 --> 00:11:55,887
门和窗子都和昨晚一样
in door or window this morning,

180
00:11:55,966 --> 00:11:57,364
也没有理由怀疑
nor any reason to think

181
00:11:57,433 --> 00:12:01,926
有陌生人进入过房子
that any stranger had been to the house.

182
00:12:02,004 --> 00:12:04,973
他们就坐在原地
Yet there they sat,

183
00:12:05,041 --> 00:12:08,806
完全被吓疯了
driven clean mad with terror.

184
00:12:08,878 --> 00:12:10,936
在我有生之年我都无法
I'll never get the sight of that room

185
00:12:11,012 --> 00:12:14,310
把那个房间的景象从我脑海中磨灭
out of my mind so long as I live.

186
00:12:14,382 --> 00:12:19,981
是啊 事实总是最深刻的
Yes, the facts are most remarkable.

187
00:12:20,654 --> 00:12:22,645
Tregennis先生你个人认为
Mr. Tregennis do you have any theory of your own

188
00:12:22,724 --> 00:12:24,384
他们为何会遭此不幸?
which might account for them?

189
00:12:24,459 --> 00:12:26,426
这是魔鬼
It is devilish.

190
00:12:26,493 --> 00:12:29,620
魔鬼 福尔摩斯先生
Devilish, Mr. Holmes.

191
00:12:29,697 --> 00:12:33,029
那力量不属于这个世界
It is not of this world.

192
00:12:33,100 --> 00:12:34,760
如果这个事件已超出人类范畴
Well the matter is beyond humanity

193
00:12:34,835 --> 00:12:36,631
那它自然也超出我的能力范围
it is certainly beyond me.

194
00:12:36,703 --> 00:12:41,509
的确如此 福尔摩斯
I trust so, Holmes.

195
00:12:44,243 --> 00:12:46,369
想想
Now think.

196
00:12:46,445 --> 00:12:49,572
仔细想一想 Tregennis先生
Think very carefully, Mr. Tregennis,

197
00:12:49,648 --> 00:12:53,014
昨晚你们在一起的时间里
about the evening that you spent together.

198
00:12:53,085 --> 00:12:55,315
你记忆里有没有什么特别的事情
Does anything stand out in your memory

199
00:12:55,387 --> 00:12:59,720
能为这场惨剧提供一点线索
which might throw some light upon this tragedy?

200
00:12:59,791 --> 00:13:02,350
没有 福尔摩斯先生
There is nothing, Mr. Holmes.

201
00:13:02,427 --> 00:13:04,758
他们是容易不安的人吗?
Were they nervous people?

202
00:13:04,829 --> 00:13:07,194
他们曾表现出任何恐惧的预兆吗?
Did they ever show any sign of apprehension?

203
00:13:07,266 --> 00:13:09,893
我认为没有 福尔摩斯先生
Not to my knowledge, Mr. Holmes.

204
00:13:09,967 --> 00:13:13,060
那你就对我的探案没什么帮助了
Then there's nothing in which you can assist me.

205
00:13:18,842 --> 00:13:21,436
我突然想起一件事
There is one thing occurs to me.

206
00:13:21,511 --> 00:13:24,969
我坐在桌边的时候背对着窗户
As I sat at the table my back was to the window,

207
00:13:25,048 --> 00:13:26,447
我的哥哥George
and my brother George,

208
00:13:26,516 --> 00:13:28,540
玩牌的时候和我一伙
he being my partner at cards,

209
00:13:28,617 --> 00:13:30,380
面朝窗户
was facing it.

210
00:13:30,452 --> 00:13:33,614
我见他有一次从我肩上看过去
I saw him once look hard over my shoulder,

211
00:13:33,690 --> 00:13:36,886
所以我也回头看了看
so I turned round and looked also.

212
00:13:36,958 --> 00:13:40,552
窗帘没拉 窗户关着
The blind was up and the window shut,

213
00:13:40,628 --> 00:13:44,461
我只能看到庭院里的矮树丛
but I could just make out the bushes on the lawn,

214
00:13:44,532 --> 00:13:45,998
但有一个瞬间
and it seemed to me for a moment

215
00:13:46,068 --> 00:13:50,060
我好像看到有什么东西在移动
that I saw something moving among them.

216
00:13:50,138 --> 00:13:53,595
说不清那是人或动物
I couldn't even say if it was man or animal,

217
00:13:53,675 --> 00:13:57,337
只是觉得有东西在那儿
but I just thought I saw something there.

218
00:13:57,412 --> 00:14:00,141
你没想要弄清楚吗?
Did you not investigate?

219
00:14:00,213 --> 00:14:02,613
当时认为没什么
Well the matter passed as unimportant.

220
00:14:02,683 --> 00:14:05,173
你看到任何恶魔的迹象吗?
Did you have any premonition of evil?

221
00:14:05,252 --> 00:14:07,048
我只是觉得
None that I was aware of.

222
00:14:07,119 --> 00:14:08,552
你怎么会这么早
How did you hear the terrible news

223
00:14:08,622 --> 00:14:10,088
就得知噩耗?
so early this morning?

224
00:14:10,157 --> 00:14:11,589
我习惯早起
I am an early riser.

225
00:14:11,657 --> 00:14:14,125
一般在早餐前散步
Generally take a walk before breakfast.

226
00:14:14,194 --> 00:14:15,683
今早我刚刚出门
This morning I had hardly started

227
00:14:15,762 --> 00:14:16,523
Richard医生
when Doctor Richard

228
00:14:16,559 --> 00:14:19,062
驾着马车找到了我
overtook me in his carriage.

229
00:14:19,130 --> 00:14:21,724
Tregennis先生
Mr. Tregennis.

230
00:14:21,801 --> 00:14:25,010
我刚从你妹妹家得知了一条紧急消息
I've just heard an urgent message from your sister's house.

231
00:14:25,004 --> 00:14:26,163
怎么了?
What's happened?

232
00:14:26,238 --> 00:14:27,670
我不是很确定
I'm not quite sure, sir,

233
00:14:27,739 --> 00:14:30,298
你最好还是跟我去一趟吧
but you'd better come with me.

234
00:14:36,748 --> 00:14:40,945
她死了至少六个小时
She's been dead at least six hours.

235
00:14:41,018 --> 00:14:45,011
没有施暴的痕迹
No signs of violence.

236
00:14:45,089 --> 00:14:48,547
但为什么?
But how?

237
00:14:48,624 --> 00:14:52,424
Tregennis先生 我从未见过这种情形
I've never seen the like, Mr. Tregennis.

238
00:14:52,495 --> 00:14:58,763
这么多年来...
Not in all my years has a...

239
00:14:58,835 --> 00:15:00,632
你还好吗?
You all right?

240
00:15:00,703 --> 00:15:02,086
我来扶着你 过来...
I've got you. Here.

241
00:15:02,660 --> 00:15:04,172
过来
Over here.

242
00:15:05,732 --> 00:15:06,868
坐下
There we go.

243
00:15:07,944 --> 00:15:10,673
他差点也在我们面前出事
We nearly got him on our hands as well.

244
00:15:15,370 --> 00:15:16,178
你要去哪儿 福尔摩斯
Where are you going Holmes?

245
00:15:16,251 --> 00:15:17,775
去Tredannick Wartha 不能耽搁
Tredannick Wartha without delay.

246
00:15:17,853 --> 00:15:19,217
福尔摩斯先生
With your permission Mr. Holmes

247
00:15:19,287 --> 00:15:19,826
请您允许我先走一步
I'll go on ahead.

248
00:15:19,862 --> 00:15:20,811
谢谢你 牧师...快点
Thank you vicar, quickly,

249
00:15:20,849 --> 00:15:22,161
否则我们就要比你先到了
otherwise we'll be there before you.

250
00:15:22,198 --> 00:15:23,139
福尔摩斯 我必须劝阻你
Holmes, I must protest.

251
00:15:23,176 --> 00:15:25,416
把你的劝阻留着吧 华生
Save your protestations for later, Watson,

252
00:15:25,559 --> 00:15:26,808
多留一会儿
much later!

253
00:15:28,262 --> 00:15:29,388
我想你因为某些原因
I gather you were divided

254
00:15:29,463 --> 00:15:30,929
和你的家庭分开了
in some way from your family.

255
00:15:30,997 --> 00:15:32,589
是的 福尔摩斯先生
Oh yes sir, Mr. Holmes.

256
00:15:32,666 --> 00:15:35,099
那已经是过去的事情了
Well the matter is past and done with.

257
00:15:35,169 --> 00:15:36,634
一切都已经被原谅和遗忘了
All was forgiven and forgotten

258
00:15:36,704 --> 00:15:38,534
我们曾是最亲密的朋友
and we were the best of friends.

259
00:15:38,605 --> 00:15:41,665
我们家曾在Redruth作锡矿工
We were a family of tin-miners at Redruth,

260
00:15:41,741 --> 00:15:44,208
但我们把家族企业卖给了一家公司
but we sold out our venture to a company,

261
00:15:44,277 --> 00:15:47,507
就此退休并有了足够的钱维持生计
and so retired with enough to keep us.

262
00:15:47,579 --> 00:15:49,308
我不否认分家产的时候
I won't deny there was some bad feeling

263
00:15:49,381 --> 00:15:51,144
有一些不愉快
over the division of the money.

264
00:15:51,216 --> 00:15:53,446
彼此间的不睦有很多年了
It stood between us for a number of years.

265
00:15:53,519 --> 00:15:55,179
不过
Nevertheless.

266
00:15:59,757 --> 00:16:01,883
你决定不离开Cornwall?
You decided not to leave Cornwall?

267
00:16:01,959 --> 00:16:03,756
我想我还怀着某天
I supposed I entertained

268
00:16:03,829 --> 00:16:07,161
欣喜的回到家人身边的希望
some hopes of returning home one day.

269
00:16:07,231 --> 00:16:08,823
福尔摩斯!
' Holmes!

270
00:16:13,371 --> 00:16:15,601
福尔摩斯 快靠边!
Holmes, stand back!

271
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:25,374
我的兄弟们
My brothers.

272
00:16:25,448 --> 00:16:27,848
他们要被送去Helston
They're taking them to Helston.

273
00:16:48,390 --> 00:16:52,832
这房子真不错 Tregennis先生
It's a lovely house, Mr. Tregennis.

274
00:16:52,907 --> 00:16:54,999
这是很悲伤的地方
It's a very sad house.

275
00:16:55,076 --> 00:16:56,407
这就是你看到
This is the window

276
00:16:56,478 --> 00:16:58,308
影子的那扇窗户
through which you saw the shadow form.

277
00:16:58,379 --> 00:17:00,888
它距离窗户大概有多远?
Approximately what distance was it from the glass?

278
00:17:04,886 --> 00:17:07,613
我想不少于10英尺
I'd say not less than ten feet.

279
00:17:07,754 --> 00:17:10,517
我感觉
With a guess,

280
00:17:10,591 --> 00:17:12,615
大概这么远
about here.

281
00:17:12,693 --> 00:17:14,523
没有强迫闯入的迹象
There's no sign of a forced entry.

282
00:17:14,594 --> 00:17:15,993
窗户当然是
And the window, of course,

283
00:17:16,062 --> 00:17:16,891
一直锁着的
would have remained locked.

284
00:17:16,963 --> 00:17:18,429
我妹妹查看它是否锁着
My sister made sure of that.

285
00:17:18,498 --> 00:17:20,193
即便在Cornwall
Even in Cornwall.

286
00:17:20,266 --> 00:17:22,165
太抱歉了
So dreadfully sorry.

287
00:17:22,235 --> 00:17:24,600
没关系 福尔摩斯先生
It's quite all right, Mr. Holmes.

288
00:17:24,669 --> 00:17:27,001
小意外
An accident.

289
00:17:36,214 --> 00:17:37,316
谢谢
Thank you.

290
00:17:39,184 --> 00:17:41,414
能告诉Porter夫人我回来了吗?
Could you let Mrs. Porter know I'm back?

291
00:18:09,546 --> 00:18:11,308
我想见见管家
I should like to meet the housekeeper.

292
00:18:11,380 --> 00:18:12,938
当然可以
Of course.

293
00:18:13,015 --> 00:18:14,642
但请尽量避免
Oh but please try to avoid

294
00:18:14,716 --> 00:18:16,808
再让她过于悲痛
causing further distress.

295
00:18:16,885 --> 00:18:20,294
死亡总是悲痛的
Death is always distressing, Mr.Tregennis.

296
00:18:20,331 --> 00:18:24,485
啊 椅子呢...
Awe, the chairs.

297
00:18:24,560 --> 00:18:25,958
在警察离开这里后
Well they must have been moved

298
00:18:26,028 --> 00:18:28,154
它们一定被移动过
after the police left the house.

299
00:18:28,229 --> 00:18:31,198
那把是在这儿 福尔摩斯先生
That one here, Mr. Holmes.

300
00:18:31,265 --> 00:18:32,596
这把在那儿
One over there.

301
00:18:32,667 --> 00:18:34,293
这个在这儿
This one here.

302
00:18:34,368 --> 00:18:38,497
这把在这儿
This one over here.

303
00:18:38,572 --> 00:18:41,597
还有什么其他东西被移动过吗?
Has anything else been moved?

304
00:18:41,675 --> 00:18:44,302
所有都跟我记忆中一样
All is as I remember it.

305
00:18:44,377 --> 00:18:45,180
你一定了解
You must understand

306
00:18:45,217 --> 00:18:47,403
今早我来这儿的时候
there was a great deal of fuss and confusion

307
00:18:47,480 --> 00:18:49,539
是多么的忙乱和困惑
when I arrived this morning.

308
00:18:49,616 --> 00:18:50,946
可能有东西被移动过
Things may have been moved

309
00:18:51,016 --> 00:18:52,198
没有想到它们在
without thought given to their significance

310
00:18:52,235 --> 00:18:53,401
犯罪调查中的重要性
in a criminal investigation.

311
00:18:53,438 --> 00:18:54,501
犯罪?
Criminal?

312
00:18:55,423 --> 00:18:57,984
这个词很有趣
That is a very interesting word.

313
00:18:58,057 --> 00:18:59,614
这么说你又不赞成
So you no longer subscribe to the theory

314
00:18:59,692 --> 00:19:04,890
所谓超自然的解释了?
of a supernatural explanation?

315
00:19:04,963 --> 00:19:06,897
我不知道
I don't know.

316
00:19:06,965 --> 00:19:09,956
大家是怎么坐的?
Where were people sitting?

317
00:19:10,034 --> 00:19:12,594
我坐在这儿 面对着Georgie
I sat here facing Georgie,

318
00:19:12,669 --> 00:19:15,035
我的哥哥
my brother George.

319
00:19:15,106 --> 00:19:17,005
Brenda挨着我
Brenda sat next to me.

320
00:19:17,074 --> 00:19:18,631
Owen对着她
Owen across from her.

321
00:19:18,709 --> 00:19:19,500
哦 这很古怪
Oh that's curious.

322
00:19:19,537 --> 00:19:20,608
怎么?
What?

323
00:19:20,645 --> 00:19:23,574
我是说从这个位置看出去
I mean from this position

324
00:19:23,647 --> 00:19:25,204
窗外的东西
the figure outside of the window

325
00:19:25,282 --> 00:19:27,836
想必要超过6英尺
must have been well over six feet.

326
00:19:30,287 --> 00:19:32,777
福尔摩斯先生 我只能如实 告诉你我所见到的
I can only tell you what I saw Mr. Holmes.

327
00:19:32,856 --> 00:19:36,347
哦 这是我们的管家
Awe, this is my housekeeper,

328
00:19:36,426 --> 00:19:38,518
Porter夫人
Mrs. Porter.

329
00:19:38,594 --> 00:19:43,326
亲爱的 我想让你见一下这些先生们
I'd like you to meet these gentlemen, my dear.

330
00:19:46,101 --> 00:19:50,162
她是那么美丽
She was so beautiful.

331
00:19:50,238 --> 00:19:54,766
那么...美...丽
So beautiful.

332
00:19:54,842 --> 00:19:57,208
她还是很难过
She is still very upset.

333
00:19:57,278 --> 00:20:00,644
我们都很难过 Roundhay先生
We're all very upset Mr. Roundhay.

334
00:20:00,714 --> 00:20:02,704
来坐下
Come and sit down.

335
00:20:02,783 --> 00:20:04,410
我不会再留在这个房子里
I will not stay in this house

336
00:20:04,485 --> 00:20:06,248
多一秒钟
one moment longer than I have to.

337
00:20:06,320 --> 00:20:12,054
我要回到自己家去
So I shall rejoin my family.

338
00:20:12,125 --> 00:20:14,389
但你也是我们家的一份子啊
But you're part of our family.

339
00:20:14,460 --> 00:20:17,918
Tregennis一家已经不在了 先生
The family Tregennis is dead, sir.

340
00:20:17,997 --> 00:20:20,658
至少是如死了一般
Dead or as good as.

341
00:20:20,733 --> 00:20:24,463
我还活着呢
I'm still alive.

342
00:20:24,537 --> 00:20:26,299
Porter夫人
Mrs. Porter,

343
00:20:30,642 --> 00:20:32,906
不好意思
excuse me now.

344
00:20:32,978 --> 00:20:34,968
Porter夫人
Mrs. Porter.

345
00:20:43,255 --> 00:20:45,222
我叫夏洛克 福尔摩斯
My name is Sherlock Holmes

346
00:20:45,290 --> 00:20:49,020
我希望你能告诉我所有你知道的事
and I'd like you to tell me all that you know.

347
00:20:49,093 --> 00:20:51,390
福尔摩斯先生是位侦探
Mr. Holmes is a detective.

348
00:20:51,462 --> 00:20:52,985
他是来想要找出
He's going to try and find out

349
00:20:53,064 --> 00:20:55,075
Brenda发生了什么 别紧张
what happened to Brenda. Don't you worry.

350
00:20:56,467 --> 00:21:00,596
请不要有所保留
Please, leave nothing out.

351
00:21:00,670 --> 00:21:04,434
我只知道很少 福尔摩斯先生
I can tell you very little, Mr. Holmes.

352
00:21:11,447 --> 00:21:13,142
你出老千
Awe, you've been cheating.

353
00:21:13,215 --> 00:21:14,841
我没有
I am not cheating.

354
00:21:14,917 --> 00:21:17,749
Owen 告诉你亲爱的妹妹
Owen will you tell your dearest sister

355
00:21:17,820 --> 00:21:19,811
按规则玩牌
to play by the rules.

356
00:21:19,888 --> 00:21:21,252
她也是你妹妹
Well she's your sister too.

357
00:21:21,323 --> 00:21:22,620
你跟她说
You tell her.

358
00:21:22,691 --> 00:21:24,817
但她是跟你一伙的
But she's on your side.

359
00:21:24,893 --> 00:21:25,570
时候不早了
It's rather late

360
00:21:25,607 --> 00:21:28,488
我得回牧师家了
and I do have to get back to the vicarage.

361
00:21:33,334 --> 00:21:36,427
Mortimer 你晚上还是留宿在这里吧
Mortimer you must stay here for the night.

362
00:21:36,503 --> 00:21:39,300
答应了吧
Oh please say you will.

363
00:21:39,373 --> 00:21:40,231
那...
Well?

364
00:21:40,267 --> 00:21:43,434
如果他不愿意就不要强迫他 Brenda
Don't force him to stay if he doesn't want to, Brenda.

365
00:21:43,471 --> 00:21:45,142
哦 是吗
Oh really,

366
00:21:45,179 --> 00:21:48,171
我以为我们的争执已经结束了呢
I thought we'd put an end to our squabbling.

367
00:21:48,247 --> 00:21:49,804
Moritimer对我来说
Mortimer is just as much my brother

368
00:21:49,882 --> 00:21:52,874
跟你和Georgie一样亲
as you and Georgie.

369
00:21:52,953 --> 00:21:54,977
不用担心 兄弟们
Don't worry, dear brother,

370
00:21:55,054 --> 00:21:56,141
我知道我不受欢迎
I know where I'm not welcome

371
00:21:56,178 --> 00:21:58,188
那干嘛还来拜访我们
Why visit us at all.

372
00:21:58,257 --> 00:21:59,554
是你离开了我们
You disowned us.

373
00:21:59,625 --> 00:22:01,217
还是你已经忘了?
Or have you have forgotten?

374
00:22:01,293 --> 00:22:02,623
Beth 这样就行了
It will be all right now, Beth,

375
00:22:02,694 --> 00:22:04,218
你可以去就寝了
if you wish to retire.

376
00:22:04,295 --> 00:22:06,660
Tregennis先生今晚会住在这里吗?
Is Mr. Tregennis staying with us tonight?

377
00:22:06,731 --> 00:22:07,891
怎么了?
Why?

378
00:22:07,967 --> 00:22:10,092
Porter夫人 你也不愿意我在这里吗?
Do you also object to my presence, Mrs. Porter?

379
00:22:10,169 --> 00:22:11,863
Mortimer
Mortimer!

380
00:22:11,936 --> 00:22:16,963
我想知道我用不用给你的房间通风
I want to know should I air your room, sir?

381
00:22:19,376 --> 00:22:21,435
抱歉
Sorry.

382
00:22:24,581 --> 00:22:25,912
谢谢你 Beth
Thank you, Beth.

383
